create new reporsitsry using command line
========================================
https://help.github.com/articles/adding-an-existing-project-to-github-using-the-command-line/
Create a new repository on GitHub with name "IPT_HM"
echo "# IPT_HM" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md(what ever u want to add. if u want to add whole then put .)
git commit -m "first commit"
git remote add origin https://github.com/Soumeniisc/IPT_HM.git
git push -u origin master

or push an existing repository from the command line
====================================================
git remote add origin https://github.com/Soumeniisc/IPT_HM.git
git push -u origin master

